    text: '\n# Principles governing required navigation performance (RNP) and air traffic service (ATS) route designators\n\n## Learning Objectives\n\n1.  **010.07.01.07.01** -- State the meaning of the acronym "RNP".\n2.  **010.07.01.07.02** -- State the factors that RNP is based on.\n3.  **010.07.01.07.03** -- Describe the reason for establishing a system of route\n    designators and navigation specifications.\n4.  **010.07.01.07.04** -- State whether or not a prescribed RNP type is\n    considered an integral part of the ATS route designator.\n5.  **010.07.01.07.05** -- Explain the composition of an ATS route designator.\n\n|                 | ATPL(A) | CPL(A) | ATPL(H)/IR | ATPL(H)/VFR | CPL(H) | IR  | CBIR(A) |\n| --------------- | ------- | ------ | ---------- | ----------- | ------ | --- | ------- |\n| 010.07.01.07.01 | X       | X      | X          | X           | X      |     |         |\n| 010.07.01.07.02 | X       | X      | X          | X           | X      |     |         |\n| 010.07.01.07.03 | X       | X      | X          | X           | X      |     |         |\n| 010.07.01.07.04 | X       | X      | X          | X           | X      |     |         |\n| 010.07.01.07.05 | X       | X      | X          | X           | X      |     |         |\n\n## Summary\n',
