    text: '\n# ATC clearances\n\n## Learning Objectives\n\n1.  **010.07.02.05.01** -- State which information the issue of an ATC clearance\n    is based on.\n2.  **010.07.02.05.02** -- Describe what a PIC should do if an ATC clearance is\n    not suitable.\n3.  **010.07.02.05.03** -- State who bears the responsibility for adhering to the\n    applicable rules and regulations whilst flying under the control of an ATC\n    unit.\n4.  **010.07.02.05.04** -- State the two primary purposes of clearances issued by\n    ATC units.\n5.  **010.07.02.05.05** -- State why clearances must be issued "early enough" to\n    aircraft.\n6.  **010.07.02.05.06** -- Explain what is meant by the expression "clearance\n    limit".\n7.  **010.07.02.05.07** -- Explain the meaning of the phrases "cleared via flight\n    planned route", "cleared via (designation) departure" and "cleared via\n    (designation) arrival" in an ATC clearance.\n8.  **010.07.02.05.08** -- List which items of an ATC clearance shall always be\n    read back by the flight crew.\n\n|                 | ATPL(A) | CPL(A) | ATPL(H)/IR | ATPL(H)/VFR | CPL(H) | IR  | CBIR(A) |\n| --------------- | ------- | ------ | ---------- | ----------- | ------ | --- | ------- |\n| 010.07.02.05.01 | X       | X      | X          | X           | X      | X   | X       |\n| 010.07.02.05.02 | X       | X      | X          | X           | X      | X   | X       |\n| 010.07.02.05.03 | X       | X      | X          | X           | X      | X   | X       |\n| 010.07.02.05.04 | X       | X      | X          | X           | X      | X   |         |\n| 010.07.02.05.05 | X       | X      | X          | X           | X      | X   |         |\n| 010.07.02.05.06 | X       | X      | X          | X           | X      | X   | X       |\n| 010.07.02.05.07 | X       | X      | X          | X           | X      | X   | X       |\n| 010.07.02.05.08 | X       | X      | X          | X           | X      | X   | X       |\n\n## Summary\n',
