  "021.01.05": {
    id: "021.01.05",
    text: '\n# Maintenance\n\n## Learning Objectives\n\n|                 | ATPL(A) | CPL(A) | ATPL(H)/IR | ATPL(H)/VFR | CPL(H) | IR  | CBIR(A) |\n| --------------- | ------- | ------ | ---------- | ----------- | ------ | --- | ------- |\n| 021.01.05.01.01 | X       | X      | X          | X           | X      |     |         |\n\n1.  **021.01.05.01.01** -- Explain the following terms: hard-time or fixed-time\n    maintenance; on-condition maintenance; condition monitoring.\n\n## Summary\n\n### Hard / Fixed time maintenance\n\nA component is replaced or overhauled after a set number of hours, cycles or\noperations, regardless of their condition.\n\n### On Condition maintenance\n\nA component is replaced or overhauled when indications of its deteriorating\ncondition are detected. For example, a maintenance check could include steps to\nvisually inspect for corrosion on specific screw heads, and as soon as it is\ndetected the whole component is replaced.\n\n### Condition monitoring\n\nSimilar to **On Condition maintenance** but leveraging modern day technology to\ncontinuously monitor specific parameters that could indicate failure.\n\n<Question id="449I12JXEM" lo="021.01.05.01.01">\n  <Text variant="oneCorrect">\n    <Subject />, is called...\n  </Text>\n\n{" "}\n<Option\n  subject={[\n    [\n      "Replacement of a part based on the number of cycles or on the time of use, regardless of its actual condition state",\n    ],\n  ]}\n>\n  Fixed time maintenance\n</Option>\n\n{" "}\n<Option\n  subject={[\n    [\n      "Replacement of a part based on the number of cycles or on the time of use, regardless of its actual condition state",\n    ],\n  ]}\n>\n  Hard time maintenance\n</Option>\n\n{" "}\n<Option\n  subject={[\n    [\n      "Using continuos means of observation to determine the optimal time to perform component maintenance",\n    ],\n  ]}\n>\n  Condition monitoring\n</Option>\n\n{" "}\n<Option\n  subject={[\n    ["Replacing a part based on indicators of its deteriorating condition"],\n  ]}\n>\n  On Condition maintenance\n</Option>\n\n  <Option\n    subject={[\n    [\n      "A component getting replaced at some point when convenient to the operator",\n    ],\n    ]}\n  >\n    Soft time maintenance\n  </Option>\n</Question>\n\n<Question id="UJ0TA4XXGK" lo="021.01.05.01.01">\n  <Text variant="oneCorrect">\n    What statement best describes <Subject />\n  </Text>\n\n{" "}\n<Option subject={[["Fixed time maintenance"], ["Hard time maintenance"]]}>\n  Replacement of a part based on the number of cycles or on accumulated\n  operation time alone\n</Option>\n\n{" "}\n<Option subject={[["Condition monitoring"]]}>\n  Using continuos means of observation to determine the optimal time to perform\n  component maintenance\n</Option>\n\n{" "}\n<Option subject={[["On Condition maintenance"]]}>\n  Monitoring of critical parameters and the replacement of parts if a limit\n  value is exceeded\n</Option>\n\n  <Option subject={[["Soft time maintenance"]]}>\n    A component getting replaced at some point when convenient to the operator\n  </Option>\n</Question>\n',
    title: "Maintenance",
    questions: [],
    los: ["021.01.05.01.01"],
  },
