    text: '\n# Fuel: types, characteristics, limitations\n\n## Learning Objectives\n\n|                 | ATPL(A) | CPL(A) | ATPL(H)/IR | ATPL(H)/VFR | CPL(H) | IR  | CBIR(A) |\n| --------------- | ------- | ------ | ---------- | ----------- | ------ | --- | ------- |\n| 021.08.01.01.01 | X       | X      | X          | X           | X      |     |         |\n| 021.08.01.01.02 | X       | X      | X          | X           | X      |     |         |\n\n1.  **021.08.01.01.01** -- State the types of fuel used by a piston engine and\n    their associated limitations: diesel; JET-A1 (for high-compression engines);\n    AVGAS; MOGAS.\n2.  **021.08.01.01.02** -- State the main characteristics of these fuels and give\n    typical values regarding their flash points, freezing points and density.\n\n## Summary\n\nMOGAS = Motor Gas, Gas that is designed for every day car usage.\n\n### Fuel for piston aircraft\n\n|                | Jet A1      | AVGAS 100 | AVGAS 100LL | AVGAS 80 |\n| -------------- | ----------- | --------- | ----------- | -------- |\n| Colour         | Transparent | Green     | Blue        | Red      |\n| Density (kg/l) | 0.80        | 0.72      | 0.72        | 0.72     |\n| Flash Point    | 38c        | ?         | ?           | ?        |\n| Freezing Point | -47C       | ?         | ?           | ?        |\n\n[Source](https://skybrary.aero/articles/ignition-fuels)\n\n<Question id="B27P8Z6JJI" lo="021.08.01.01.01">\n  <Text variant="oneCorrect">\n    Using MOGAS in a piston engine aircraft instead of AVGAS...\n  </Text>\n\n{" "}\n<Text variant="oneTwo">\n  Using MOGAS in a piston engine aircraft instead of AVGAS...\n</Text>\n\n{" "}\n<Text variant="multipleCorrect" select={4}>\n  Using MOGAS in a piston engine aircraft instead of AVGAS...\n</Text>\n\n{" "}\n<Option correct>increases the risk of Carburettor Icing</Option>\n<Option correct>increases the risk of Engine Fire</Option>\n<Option correct>increases the risk of Detonation Fire</Option>\n<Option>lowers the risk of engine fire</Option>\n<Option>lowers the risk of Carburettor icing</Option>\n\n  <Option why="it will decrease the maximum MAP since detonation will occur at a lower pressure">\n    increases Manifold pressure\n  </Option>\n</Question>\n',
