    text: "\n# Temperature sensing\n\n## Learning Objectives\n\n|                 | ATPL(A) | CPL(A) | ATPL(H)/IR | ATPL(H)/VFR | CPL(H) | IR  | CBIR(A) |\n| --------------- | ------- | ------ | ---------- | ----------- | ------ | --- | ------- |\n| 022.01.02.01.01 | X       | X      | X          | X           | X      |     |         |\n| 022.01.02.01.02 | X       | X      | X          | X           | X      |     |         |\n| 022.01.02.01.03 | X       | X      | X          | X           | X      |     |         |\n| 022.01.02.01.04 | X       | X      | X          | X           | X      |     |         |\n| 022.01.02.01.05 | X       | X      | X          | X           | X      |     |         |\n\n1.  **022.01.02.01.01** -- Explain temperature.\n2.  **022.01.02.01.02** -- List the following units that can be used for\n    temperature measurement: Kelvin; Celsius; Fahrenheit.\n3.  **022.01.02.01.03** -- State the relationship between these units and convert\n    between them.\n4.  **022.01.02.01.04** -- Identify temperature measurements that are applicable\n    to an aircraft: gas temperature measurement (ambient air, bleed-air systems,\n    air-conditioning systems, air inlet, exhaust gas, gas turbine outlets);\n    liquid-temperature measurement (fuel, oil, hydraulic); component-temperature\n    measurement (generator, transformer rectifier unit (TRU), pumps (fuel,\n    hydraulic), power transfer unit (PTU).\n5.  **022.01.02.01.05** -- Identify and read temperature measurement indications\n    for both engine indications and other systems.\n\n## Summary\n",
