    text: '\n# Fuel flowmeters\n\n## Learning Objectives\n\n1.  **022.01.04.01.01** -- Define "fuel flow" and where it is measured.\n2.  **022.01.04.01.02** -- State that fuel flow may be measured by volume or mass\n    per unit of time.\n3.  **022.01.04.01.03** -- List the following units used for fuel flow when\n    measured by mass per hour: kilogrammes/hour; pounds/hour.\n4.  **022.01.04.01.04** -- List the following units used for fuel flow when\n    measured by volume per hour: litres/hour; imperial gallons/hour; US\n    gallons/hour.\n5.  **022.01.04.01.05** -- Explain how total fuel consumption is obtained.\n\n|                 | ATPL(A) | CPL(A) | ATPL(H)/IR | ATPL(H)/VFR | CPL(H) | IR  | CBIR(A) |\n| --------------- | ------- | ------ | ---------- | ----------- | ------ | --- | ------- |\n| 022.01.04.01.01 | X       | X      | X          | X           | X      |     |         |\n| 022.01.04.01.02 | X       | X      | X          | X           | X      |     |         |\n| 022.01.04.01.03 | X       | X      | X          | X           | X      |     |         |\n| 022.01.04.01.04 | X       | X      | X          | X           | X      |     |         |\n| 022.01.04.01.05 | X       | X      | X          | X           | X      |     |         |\n\n## Summary\n',
