  "022.01.08": {
    id: "022.01.08",
    text: '\n# Synchroscope\n\n## Learning Objectives\n\n1.  **022.01.08.01.01** -- State the purpose of a synchroscope.\n2.  **022.01.08.01.02** -- Explain the operating principle of a synchroscope.\n3.  **022.01.08.01.03** -- Give examples of display.\n\n|                 | ATPL(A) | CPL(A) | ATPL(H)/IR | ATPL(H)/VFR | CPL(H) | IR  | CBIR(A) |\n| --------------- | ------- | ------ | ---------- | ----------- | ------ | --- | ------- |\n| 022.01.08.01.01 | X       | X      |            |             |        |     |         |\n| 022.01.08.01.02 | X       | X      |            |             |        |     |         |\n| 022.01.08.01.03 | X       | X      |            |             |        |     |         |\n\n## Summary\n\n<Question id="HOD2FIWP2U" lo={["022.01.08.01.01"]}>\n  <Text variant="oneCorrect">What is the purpose of a synchroscope?</Text>\n  <Text variant="oneTwo">What is the purpose of a synchroscope?</Text>\n\n{" "}\n<Text variant="multipleCorrect" select={4}>\n  What is the purpose of a synchroscope?\n</Text>\n\n{" "}\n<Option subject={[[]]}>Reduce vibrations</Option>\n<Option subject={[[]]}>Avoid asymmetric flight conditions</Option>\n<Option subject={[[]]}>Reduce fuel consumption</Option>\n<Option subject={[[]]}>Synchronize Engine/Propeller Speed</Option>\n\n{" "}\n<Option why="The goal is to reduce fuel consumption and synchronize propeller speed. This might not equate to a synchronization of fuel consumption. Imagine the case of having one engine with poorer performance. That engine will have a higher consumption in order to maintain the propellers synchronized">\n  Synchronize fuel consumption\n</Option>\n\n  <Option why="The synchroscope reduces vibrations caused by having 2 engines running at slightly different frequencies. It has no usefulness to reduce vibrations of a single engine.">\n    Remove vibrations from an engine.\n  </Option>\n</Question>\n\n<Question id="HOD2FIWP3U" lo={["022.01.08.01.01", "022.01.08.01.02"]}>\n  <Text variant="oneCorrect">\n    Which statement best describes the working principle of a Synchroscope?\n  </Text>\n\n{" "}\n<Text variant="oneTwo">What statements about a synchroscope are correct?</Text>\n\n{" "}\n<Text variant="multipleCorrect" select={4}>\n  What statements about a synchroscope are correct?\n</Text>\n\n{" "}\n<Option subject={[[]]}>\n  It measures the difference in output frequencies of alternators placed in each\n  engine.\n</Option>\n\n{" "}\n<Option subject={[[]]}>\n  It consists of a voltmeter which is fed by two tachometer-generators\n</Option>\n\n{" "}\n<Option subject={[[]]}>\n  It provides information required to set several engines at the same rotational\n  speed\n</Option>\n\n{" "}\n<Option subject={[[]]}>It gives information about engine speed</Option>\n\n{" "}\n<Option why="A synchroscope provides engine speed in an adimensional fashion (ie.: Faster and slower).">\n  It gives information about engine speed in RPM\n</Option>\n\n{" "}\n<Option why="A synchroscope provides engine speed in an adimensional fashion (ie.: Faster and slower).">\n  It gives information about engine speed in HZ\n</Option>\n\n{" "}\n<Option why="A synchroscope provides information on engine speed not power">\n  It gives information about engine power\n</Option>\n\n{" "}\n<Option why="The synchroscope allows to synchronize the RPM of 2 engines, but it does not measure RPM. rather it measures frequency generated by an alternator.">\n  It mathematically subtracts RPM values of both engines\n</Option>\n\n{" "}\n<Option why="The synchroscope exists to reduce vibrations caused by out of sync engines, but it does not measure vibrations directly.">\n  It measures the vibration values of both engines with a piezoelectric sensor\n</Option>\n\n{" "}\n<Option why="The synchroscope exists to reduce vibrations caused by out of sync engines, but it does not measure vibrations directly.">\n  It mathematically subtracts vibration values of both engines\n</Option>\n\n{" "}\n<Option why="A Galvonmeter is an old-school ammeter (measures amperage). A synchroscope measures a frequency difference of 2 alternators and not their current.">\n  It consists of a galvonmeter which is fed by two alternators\n</Option>\n\n  <Option why="A synchroscope simply measures the different rotation speeds of 2 engines. It does not create a communication channel directly between the 2 engines.">\n    A rotor from one engine is sending frequencies to the stator of the other\n    engine.\n  </Option>\n</Question>\n',
    title: "Synchroscope",
    questions: [],
    los: ["022.01.08.01.01", "022.01.08.01.02", "022.01.08.01.03"],
  },
