    text: "\n# Aircraft magnetic field\n\n## Learning Objectives\n\n1.  **022.03.02.01.01** -- Explain the following differences between permanent\n    magnetism and electromagnetism: when they are present; what affects their\n    magnitude.\n2.  **022.03.02.01.02** -- Explain the principles of and the reasons for: compass\n    swinging (determination of initial deviations); compass compensation\n    (correction of deviations found); compass calibration (determination of\n    residual deviations).\n3.  **022.03.02.01.03** -- Explain how permanent magnetism within the aircraft\n    structure and electromagnetism from the aircraft systems affect the accuracy\n    of a compass.\n4.  **022.03.02.01.04** -- Describe the purpose and the use of a deviation\n    correction card.\n5.  **022.03.02.01.05** -- Demonstrate the use of deviation values (either given\n    as E/W or +/) from a compass deviation card to calculate: compass heading to\n    magnetic heading; magnetic heading to compass heading.\n\n|                 | ATPL(A) | CPL(A) | ATPL(H)/IR | ATPL(H)/VFR | CPL(H) | IR  | CBIR(A) |\n| --------------- | ------- | ------ | ---------- | ----------- | ------ | --- | ------- |\n| 022.03.02.01.01 | X       | X      | X          | X           | X      | X   |         |\n| 022.03.02.01.02 | X       | X      | X          | X           | X      | X   |         |\n| 022.03.02.01.03 | X       | X      | X          | X           | X      | X   |         |\n| 022.03.02.01.04 | X       | X      | X          | X           | X      | X   |         |\n| 022.03.02.01.05 | X       | X      | X          | X           | X      | X   | X       |\n\n## Summary\n",
