    text: "\n# Purpose, architecture, failures, functions\n\n## Learning Objectives\n\n1.  **022.11.01.01.01** -- Explain the purpose of an FMS.\n2.  **022.11.01.01.02** -- Describe a typical dual FMS architecture including the\n    following components: flight management computer (FMC); CDU/MCDU; cross-talk\n    bus.\n3.  **022.11.01.01.03** -- Describe the following failures of a dual FMS\n    architecture and explain the potential implications to the pilots: failure of\n    one FMC; failure of one CDU/MCDU; failure of the cross-talk bus.\n4.  **022.11.01.01.04** -- Describe how the FMS integrates with other systems and\n    gathers data in order to provide outputs depending on its level of\n    complexity.\n5.  **022.11.01.01.05** -- Explain how the FMS may provide the following\n    functions: navigation; lateral and vertical flight planning; performance\n    parameters.\n\n|                 | ATPL(A) | CPL(A) | ATPL(H)/IR | ATPL(H)/VFR | CPL(H) | IR  | CBIR(A) |\n| --------------- | ------- | ------ | ---------- | ----------- | ------ | --- | ------- |\n| 022.11.01.01.01 | X       |        | X          | X           |        | X   |         |\n| 022.11.01.01.02 | X       |        | X          | X           |        |     |         |\n| 022.11.01.01.03 | X       |        | X          | X           |        |     |         |\n| 022.11.01.01.04 | X       |        | X          | X           |        | X   |         |\n| 022.11.01.01.05 | X       | X      | X          | X           |        | X   |         |\n\n## Summary\n",
