    text: '\n# Hearing\n\n## Learning Objectives\n\n1.  **040.02.02.04.01** -- State the basic parts and functions of the outer, the\n    middle and the inner ear.\n2.  **040.02.02.04.02** -- Differentiate between the functions of the vestibular\n    apparatus and the cochlea in the inner ear.\n3.  **040.02.02.04.03** -- Define the main causes of the following hearing\n    defects/loss: "conductive deafness"; "noise-induced hearing loss" (NIHL);\n    "presbycusis".\n4.  **040.02.02.04.04** -- Summarise the effects of environmental noise on\n    hearing.\n5.  **040.02.02.04.05** -- State the decibel level of received noise that will\n    cause NIHL.\n6.  **040.02.02.04.06** -- Identify the potential occupational risks that may\n    cause hearing loss.\n7.  **040.02.02.04.07** -- List the main sources of hearing loss in the flying\n    environment.\n8.  **040.02.02.04.08** -- List the precautions that may be taken to reduce the\n    probability of onset of hearing loss.\n\n|                 | ATPL(A) | CPL(A) | ATPL(H)/IR | ATPL(H)/VFR | CPL(H) | IR  | CBIR(A) |\n| --------------- | ------- | ------ | ---------- | ----------- | ------ | --- | ------- |\n| 040.02.02.04.01 | X       | X      | X          | X           | X      | X   |         |\n| 040.02.02.04.02 | X       | X      | X          | X           | X      | X   |         |\n| 040.02.02.04.03 | X       | X      | X          | X           | X      | X   |         |\n| 040.02.02.04.04 | X       | X      | X          | X           | X      | X   |         |\n| 040.02.02.04.05 | X       | X      | X          | X           | X      | X   |         |\n| 040.02.02.04.06 | X       | X      | X          | X           | X      | X   |         |\n| 040.02.02.04.07 | X       | X      | X          | X           | X      | X   |         |\n| 040.02.02.04.08 | X       | X      | X          | X           | X      | X   |         |\n\n## Summary\n',
