    text: "\n# WGS-84 ellipsoid\n\n## Learning Objectives\n\n1.  **061.01.04.01.01** -- State that 1 NM is equal to 1 852 km, which is the\n    average distance of 1' of latitude change on the WGS-84 ellipsoid.\n2.  **061.01.04.01.02** -- State that 1' of longitude change at the equator on\n    the WGS-84 ellipsoid is approximately equal to 1 NM.\n\n|                 | ATPL(A) | CPL(A) | ATPL(H)/IR | ATPL(H)/VFR | CPL(H) | IR  | CBIR(A) |\n| --------------- | ------- | ------ | ---------- | ----------- | ------ | --- | ------- |\n| 061.01.04.01.01 | X       | X      | X          | X           | X      |     |         |\n| 061.01.04.01.02 | X       | X      | X          | X           | X      |     |         |\n\n## Summary\n",
