  "061.04.01.02": {
    id: "061.04.01.02",
    text: '\n# Convergence\n\n## Learning Objectives\n\n1.  **061.04.01.02.01** -- Explain and calculate the constant of the cone (sine\n    of parallel of origin).\n2.  **061.04.01.02.02** -- Explain the relationship between Earth and chart\n    convergence with respect to the ICAO requirement for a straight line to\n    approximate a great circle.\n\n|                 | ATPL(A) | CPL(A) | ATPL(H)/IR | ATPL(H)/VFR | CPL(H) | IR  | CBIR(A) |\n| --------------- | ------- | ------ | ---------- | ----------- | ------ | --- | ------- |\n| 061.04.01.02.01 | X       | X      | X          | X           | X      |     |         |\n| 061.04.01.02.02 | X       | X      | X          | X           | X      |     |         |\n\n## Summary\n\n### Chart vs Earth convergence\n\nEarth meridian convergence is the difference in inclination between two\nmeridians on the earth or the change in true track (direction) of a **great\ncircle** between two meridians on the earth.\n\nChart meridian convergence is the difference in inclination between two\nmeridians on a chart or the change in true track (direction) of a **straight\nline** between two meridians on a chart.\n\n<Question id="ES4GXW5SAZ" lo={["061.04.01.02.02"]} contentRef="### Chart vs Earth convergence">\n  <Text variant="oneCorrect">\n    A <Subject /> is drawn between two points on a chart. The change in true\n    track is 20.\n  </Text>\n\n{" "}\n<Option subject={[["straight line"]]}>Chart meridian convergence is 20</Option>\n\n{" "}\n<Option subject={[["great circle"]]}>Earth meridian convergence is 20</Option>\n\n{" "}\n<Option why="This option never makes sense. If the change in true track is 20, the convergence is 20.">\n  Chart meridian convergence is 10\n</Option>\n\n  <Option why="This option never makes sense. If the change in true track is 20, the convergence is 20.">\n    Earth meridian convergence is 10\n  </Option>\n</Question>\n',
    title: "Convergence",
    questions: [],
    los: ["061.04.01.02.01", "061.04.01.02.02"],
  },
