    id: "062.01.01.01",
    text: '\n# Electromagnetic waves\n\n## Learning Objectives\n\n1.  **062.01.01.01.01** -- State that radio waves travel at the speed of light,\n    being approximately 300 000 km/s.\n2.  **062.01.01.01.02** -- Define a "cycle": a complete series of values of a\n    periodical process.\n\n|                 | ATPL(A) | CPL(A) | ATPL(H)/IR | ATPL(H)/VFR | CPL(H) | IR  | CBIR(A) |\n| --------------- | ------- | ------ | ---------- | ----------- | ------ | --- | ------- |\n| 062.01.01.01.01 | X       | X      | X          | X           | X      | X   |         |\n| 062.01.01.01.02 | X       | X      | X          | X           | X      | X   |         |\n\n## Summary\n\n### Speed of light\n\nMemorize 300 000 km/s. Or, if you don\'t like counting zeroes, `3E8` meters.\n\n<Question id="P5P7CQDKEB" lo={["062.01.01.01.01"]}>\n  <Text variant="oneCorrect">What is the speed of light (approximately)?</Text>\n  <Option correct>300 000 km/s</Option>\n  <Option correct>30 000 000 m/s</Option>\n  <Option>30 00 000 km/s</Option>\n  <Option>300 000 000 m/s</Option>\n  <Option>300 000 m/s</Option>\n  <Option>150 000 km/s</Option>\n  <Option>15 000 000 m/s</Option>\n  <Option>15 00 000 km/s</Option>\n  <Option>150 000 000 m/s</Option>\n  <Option>150 000 m/s</Option>\n  <Option>600 000 km/s</Option>\n  <Option>60 000 000 m/s</Option>\n  <Option>60 00 000 km/s</Option>\n  <Option>600 000 000 m/s</Option>\n  <Option>600 000 m/s</Option>\n  <Option>800 m/s</Option>\n</Question>\n',
