    id: "062.02.01.02",
    text: '\n# Presentation and interpretation\n\n## Learning Objectives\n\n1.  **062.02.01.02.01** -- Define the term "QDM": the magnetic bearing to the\n    station.\n2.  **062.02.01.02.02** -- Define the term "QDR": the magnetic bearing from the\n    station.\n3.  **062.02.01.02.03** -- Explain that by using more than one ground station,\n    the position of an aircraft can be determined and transmitted to the pilot.\n\n|                 | ATPL(A) | CPL(A) | ATPL(H)/IR | ATPL(H)/VFR | CPL(H) | IR  | CBIR(A) |\n| --------------- | ------- | ------ | ---------- | ----------- | ------ | --- | ------- |\n| 062.02.01.02.01 | X       | X      | X          | X           | X      | X   | X       |\n| 062.02.01.02.02 | X       | X      | X          | X           | X      | X   | X       |\n| 062.02.01.02.03 | X       | X      | X          | X           | X      | X   |         |\n\n## Summary\n\n<Question id="FPVT3TZPXK" lo={["062.02.01.02.01", "062.02.01.02.02"]}>\n  <Text variant="oneCorrect">\n    What is the Q code for a <Subject />\n  </Text>\n\n{" "}\n<Option subject={[["Magnetic Bearing from a VDF station"]]}>QDR</Option>\n<Option subject={[["Magnetic Bearing to a VDF station"]]}>QDM</Option>\n<Option subject={[["True Bearing from a VDF station"]]}>QTE</Option>\n<Option subject={[["True Bearing to a VDF"]]}>QUJ</Option>\n\n  <Explanation>\n    Each country / language ends up coming up to mnemonics to memorize these. I\n    ended up going with the spanish one (despite not being a spanish speaker\n    myself): - QDM - Q de Morro - Q "in the head" - Magnetic with the station in\n    front of you - QDR - Q de Rabo - Q "from the arse" - Magnetic with the\n    station in your arse. For the True bearings, I just remember that `it\'s CUTE\n            (QTE) to go away from the station`. `QUJ` is the one that is left after\n    that. If you have better mnemonics... please contribute :)\n  </Explanation>\n</Question>\n',
