    text: "\n# Ground radar\n\n## Learning Objectives\n\n1.  **062.03.02.01.01** -- Explain that primary radar provides bearing and\n    distance of targets.\n2.  **062.03.02.01.02** -- Explain that primary ground radar is used to detect\n    aircraft that are not equipped with a secondary radar transponder.\n3.  **062.03.02.02.01** -- State that modern ATC systems use inputs from various\n    sensors to generate the display.\n\n|                 | ATPL(A) | CPL(A) | ATPL(H)/IR | ATPL(H)/VFR | CPL(H) | IR  | CBIR(A) |\n| --------------- | ------- | ------ | ---------- | ----------- | ------ | --- | ------- |\n| 062.03.02.01.01 | X       |        | X          | X           |        | X   | X       |\n| 062.03.02.01.02 | X       |        | X          | X           |        | X   | X       |\n| 062.03.02.02.01 | X       |        | X          | X           |        | X   | X       |\n\n## Summary\n",
    title: "Ground radar",
    questions: [],
    los: ["062.03.02.01.01", "062.03.02.01.02", "062.03.02.02.01"],
