    id: "062.07.04.02",
    text: "\n# On-board performance monitoring and alerting\n\n## Learning Objectives\n\n1.  **062.07.04.02.01** -- State that on-board performance monitoring and\n    alerting of flight technical errors is managed by on-board systems or flight\n    crew procedures.\n2.  **062.07.04.02.02** -- State that on-board performance monitoring and\n    alerting of navigation system errors is a requirement of on-board equipment\n    for RNP.\n3.  **062.07.04.02.03** -- State that, dependent on the navigation sensor, the\n    estimated position error (EPE) is compared with the required navigation\n    specification.\n4.  **062.07.04.02.04** -- Explain how a navigation system assesses the EPE.\n5.  **062.07.04.02.05** -- Give an example of how the loss of the ability to\n    operate in RNP airspace may be indicated by the navigation system.\n6.  **062.07.04.02.06** -- State that on-board performance monitoring and\n    alerting of path definition error is managed by gross reasonableness checks\n    of navigation data.\n\n|                 | ATPL(A) | CPL(A) | ATPL(H)/IR | ATPL(H)/VFR | CPL(H) | IR  | CBIR(A) |\n| --------------- | ------- | ------ | ---------- | ----------- | ------ | --- | ------- |\n| 062.07.04.02.01 | X       |        | X          |             |        | X   | X       |\n| 062.07.04.02.02 | X       |        | X          |             |        | X   | X       |\n| 062.07.04.02.03 | X       |        | X          |             |        | X   |         |\n| 062.07.04.02.04 | X       |        | X          |             |        | X   |         |\n| 062.07.04.02.05 | X       |        | X          |             |        | X   |         |\n| 062.07.04.02.06 | X       |        | X          |             |        | X   | X       |\n\n## Summary\n",
