    text: "\n# Induced drag\n\n## Learning Objectives\n\n1.  **081.01.04.03.01** -- Explain the factors that cause induced drag.\n2.  **081.01.04.03.02** -- Describe the approximate formula for the induced drag\n    coefficient (including variables but excluding constants).\n3.  **081.01.04.03.03** -- Describe the relationship between induced drag and\n    total drag in straight and level flight with variable speed.\n4.  **081.01.04.03.04** -- Describe the effect of mass on induced drag at a given\n    IAS.\n5.  **081.01.04.03.05** -- Describe the means to reduce induced drag: aspect\n    ratio; winglets; tip tanks; wing twist; camber change.\n6.  **081.01.04.03.06** -- Describe the influence of lift distribution on induced\n    drag.\n7.  **081.01.04.03.07** -- Describe the influence of downwash on the effective\n    airflow.\n8.  **081.01.04.03.08** -- Explain induced and effective local alpha.\n9.  **081.01.04.03.09** -- Explain the influence of the induced alpha on the\n    direction of the lift vector.\n10. **081.01.04.03.10** -- Explain the relationship between induced drag and:\n    speed; aspect ratio; wing planform; bank angle in a horizontal coordinated\n    turn.\n11. **081.01.04.03.11** -- Explain the induced drag coefficient and its\n    relationship with the lift coefficient and aspect ratio.\n12. **081.01.04.03.12** -- Explain the influence of induced drag on: the\n    CL-alpha graph, and show the effect on the graph when comparing high- and\n    low-aspect ratio wings; the CL-CD (aeroplane polar), and show the effect on\n    the graph when comparing high- and low-aspect ratio wings; the parabolic\n    aeroplane polar in a graph and as a formula **CD equals CPD plus kCL2**,\n    where CD equals coefficient of drag and CPD equals coefficient of parasite\n    drag.\n13. **081.01.04.03.13** -- Describe the CL-CD graph (polar).\n14. **081.01.04.03.14** -- Indicate minimum drag on the graph.\n15. **081.01.04.03.15** -- Explain why the CL-CD ratio is important as a measure\n    of performance.\n16. **081.01.04.03.16** -- Intentionally left blank\n\n|                 | ATPL(A) | CPL(A) | ATPL(H)/IR | ATPL(H)/VFR | CPL(H) | IR  | CBIR(A) |\n| --------------- | ------- | ------ | ---------- | ----------- | ------ | --- | ------- |\n| 081.01.04.03.01 | X       | X      |            |             |        |     |         |\n| 081.01.04.03.02 | X       | X      |            |             |        |     |         |\n| 081.01.04.03.03 | X       | X      |            |             |        |     |         |\n| 081.01.04.03.04 | X       | X      |            |             |        |     |         |\n| 081.01.04.03.05 | X       | X      |            |             |        |     |         |\n| 081.01.04.03.06 | X       | X      |            |             |        |     |         |\n| 081.01.04.03.07 | X       | X      |            |             |        |     |         |\n| 081.01.04.03.08 | X       | X      |            |             |        |     |         |\n| 081.01.04.03.09 | X       | X      |            |             |        |     |         |\n| 081.01.04.03.10 | X       | X      |            |             |        |     |         |\n| 081.01.04.03.11 | X       | X      |            |             |        |     |         |\n| 081.01.04.03.12 | X       | X      |            |             |        |     |         |\n| 081.01.04.03.13 | X       | X      |            |             |        |     |         |\n| 081.01.04.03.14 | X       | X      |            |             |        |     |         |\n| 081.01.04.03.15 | X       | X      |            |             |        |     |         |\n| 081.01.04.03.16 |         |        |            |             |        |     |         |\n\n## Summary\n",
