    text: "\n# Influence of temperature and altitude on Mach number\n\n## Learning Objectives\n\n1.  **081.02.01.03.01** -- Explain the absence of change of Mach number with\n    varying temperature at constant flight level and calibrated airspeed.\n2.  **081.02.01.03.02** -- Explain the relationship between Mach number, TAS and\n    IAS during climb and descent at constant Mach number or IAS, and explain\n    variation of lift coefficient, alpha, pitch and flight-path angle.\n3.  **081.02.01.03.03** -- Explain: risk of exceeding the maximum operation speed\n    (VMO) when descending at constant Mach number; risk of exceeding the maximum\n    operating Mach number (MMO) when climbing at constant IAS; risk of a\n    low-speed stall at high altitude when climbing at a too low Mach number.\n\n|                 | ATPL(A) | CPL(A) | ATPL(H)/IR | ATPL(H)/VFR | CPL(H) | IR  | CBIR(A) |\n| --------------- | ------- | ------ | ---------- | ----------- | ------ | --- | ------- |\n| 081.02.01.03.01 | X       |        |            |             |        |     |         |\n| 081.02.01.03.02 | X       |        |            |             |        |     |         |\n| 081.02.01.03.03 | X       |        |            |             |        |     |         |\n\n## Summary\n",
