    text: '\n# Anti-torque force and tail rotor\n\n## Learning Objectives\n\n1.  **082.04.01.02.01** -- Using Newton"s third law (motion), explain the need\n    for tail-rotor thrust, the required value being proportional to main-rotor\n    torque. Show that tail-rotor power is proportional to tail-rotor thrust.\n2.  **082.04.01.02.02** -- Explain the necessity for feathering of the tail-rotor\n    blades and their control by the yaw pedals, and the maximum and minimum\n    values of the pitch angles of the blades.\n\n|                 | ATPL(A) | CPL(A) | ATPL(H)/IR | ATPL(H)/VFR | CPL(H) | IR  | CBIR(A) |\n| --------------- | ------- | ------ | ---------- | ----------- | ------ | --- | ------- |\n| 082.04.01.02.01 |         |        | X          | X           | X      |     |         |\n| 082.04.01.02.02 |         |        | X          | X           | X      |     |         |\n\n## Summary\n',
